{
  "stem": "25831.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I became aware of it in 1932 when some of my friends-- there were hardly any Jews in my class at that time-- when some of my friends told me-- who belonged to the Hitler Youth-- told me that they learned what kind of methods to use to make people confess.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And one, my best friend told me, that they experimented with dropping water from an eyedropper into people's ears to see how soon they become disoriented and dizzy.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I said to him, do they teach other things like this too?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He said, yes, lots of things.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- but I didn't take it very seriously.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But in 1933-- 4-- 1934, that same friend said to me, you know, you better get out of Germany.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It's going to be terrible for Jews.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And when I came home and I told that to my father, he said, not to us, it won't be, you know.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I was a veteran from the war.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I have the Iron Cross.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My brother has the Iron Cross.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I always voted conservative German-- they won't to do anything to me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I said, you know, you don't hear the bad stuff because everybody kowtows to you.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "When he walks down the street, people bow.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Nobody would tell him what the-- what the general feeling is.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Of course, at that time, it was only a feeling.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Because the Wannsee Conference, you know, which made the decision to exterminate, where the decision to exterminate the Jews was formalized, happened only many years later.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So I can understand my father for not wanting to leave this cushioned life because he didn't suffer from this anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I didn't suffer either, but I heard about it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, we had-- we had--",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
